experiences.detail:
+ Be responsible for operation of ticket office with over 20 staffs in top-quality amusement park for tourists and relaxing guests;
+ Work with travel agents, check booking and payment accordingly;
+ Make working schedule for staff and monitor their compliances;
+ Co-work with internal departments, such as : sales, accountant, finance, security to make sure all documents, receipts are correct;
+ Event preparation : coordinate with relevant parties to ensure all events go through smoothly; carry out the logistic work in pre-event stage;
+ Control cost and budget that allocated to the department;
+ Take care of guest, handle complaints effectively. Facilitate a good environment for guest’s enjoyment.
+ The tasks of an office admin : prepare financial reports and send them to designated departments / persons.

+ Monitor staff, make sure (that) they follow company's procedure and policy;
+ Update information on computer’s system as required;
+ In case of dispute with guest, try to find mutual solution to maintain guest’s satisfaction.

) + Manage staff during their working hours (assign duty, break time, etc.);
+ Office duties is a part of my job : edit documents, write email, data storage, etc.
+ The regular customer service duties, such as : welcome guests, communicate with guest and try to meet their demand as much as possible;
+ In case of dispute, try to find mutual solution for customer without violation of company’s procedure and policy;
+ Make the reports in accordance with company’s requirements.
